HEADWORD: Underpitch
<hw>Un`der*pitch"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Underpight</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>underpicchen</ets>. See <er>Under</er>, and <er>Pitch</er> to
throw, fix.]</ety> <def>To fill underneath; to stuff.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He drank and well his girdle <qex>underpight</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

